NEW ORLEANS -- Brandon Weeden continues his quest for his first win as the Dallas Cowboys' starting quarterback tonight in New Orleans. 
Weeden's counterpart, Drew Brees, started the game after missing the Saints' Week 3 game with a shoulder injury. The Saints are looking for their first win of 2015. 
The Cowboys opened the scoring with a 74-yard drive that ended in a Dan Bailey field goal, but New Orleans bounced back with an 11-play, 80-yard touchdown drive to take a 7-3 lead. Get live updates on game action here . Click here for the box score and statistics.
